      <description>&lt;p&gt;Welcome to Wenjun Zhang&#39;s homepage! I am a senior year undergraduate student at Peking University. My research interests include atomic, molecular and optical (AMO) physics and quantum simulation. In particular, ultracold systems are clean and highly tunable, making them perfect platforms to perform quantum simulation and high-precision metrology. Since my sophomore year, I did several research projects on ultracold quantum gases, optical lattices, matter-wave interferometer, and spin chains. &lt;strong&gt;Now I am seeking for a Ph.D. position&lt;/strong&gt; in physics or applied physics, and I hope to do some research on many-body physics or optical lattice orbital physics or dynamics with ultracold systems.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
